1
00:00:09,375 --> 00:00:11,011
Karen: <i>It's been three months</i>

2
00:00:11,077 --> 00:00:12,979
<i>since I moved</i>
<i>from home in Hokkaido</i>

3
00:00:13,046 --> 00:00:15,248
<i>to Tokyo to go</i>
<i>to a women's college.</i>

4
00:00:16,650 --> 00:00:19,753
<i>I thought things would be</i>
<i>different for me in Tokyo.</i>

5
00:00:19,820 --> 00:00:23,356
<i>At least, I hoped they'd be,</i>

6
00:00:23,423 --> 00:00:26,359
<i>but things are still the same,</i>
<i>like they were at home.</i>

7
00:00:26,426 --> 00:00:30,496
<i>For one,</i>
<i>I'm still as tall as ever.</i>

8
00:00:32,733 --> 00:00:34,568
<i>I haven't made</i>
<i>any friends at school</i>

9
00:00:34,635 --> 00:00:36,637
<i>and haven't joined</i>
<i>any clubs, either,</i>

10
00:00:36,703 --> 00:00:39,405
<i>and my folks still won't let me</i>
<i>get a part‐time job,</i>

11
00:00:39,472 --> 00:00:41,675
<i>so every day's</i>
<i>the same old story.</i>

12
00:00:41,742 --> 00:00:44,444
<i>I go to school,</i>
<i>then back to my apartment.</i>

13
00:00:44,511 --> 00:00:46,212
[gasps]

14
00:00:46,279 --> 00:00:49,282
‐ Don't forget!
We're gonna meet at 1800!

15
00:00:49,349 --> 00:00:50,951
Girls: Okay! [giggling]

16
00:00:51,017 --> 00:00:54,354
‐ <i>They're so lucky to be</i>
<i>short and cute like that.</i>

17
00:00:54,420 --> 00:00:57,758
<i>If I was like them,</i>
<i>my life would be way different,</i>

18
00:00:57,824 --> 00:00:59,359
‐ and way bet‐‐
‐ [clang]

19
00:00:59,425 --> 00:01:01,427
[groans]

20
00:01:01,494 --> 00:01:03,429
‐ Oh, my goodness!
are you okay?!

21
00:01:03,496 --> 00:01:06,533
‐ Yeah.
This always happens to me.

22
00:01:06,600 --> 00:01:07,734
[laughs]

23
00:01:07,801 --> 00:01:09,736
["Ryusei" by Eir Aoi playing]

24
00:01:22,048 --> 00:01:24,184
‐ [singing in Japanese]

25
00:01:56,316 --> 00:01:57,250
<i>♪ ...safety ♪</i>

26
00:01:57,317 --> 00:01:59,252
[singing in Japanese]

27
00:02:25,912 --> 00:02:28,381
<i>♪ The darkest night ♪</i>

28
00:02:28,448 --> 00:02:30,584
[singing in Japanese]

29
00:02:32,485 --> 00:02:36,657
<i>♪ The darkest night ♪</i>

30
00:02:41,327 --> 00:02:44,164
Karen: <i>I got into VR games</i>
<i>during summer vacation.</i>

31
00:02:44,230 --> 00:02:46,466
<i>When I was back home</i>
<i>visiting the folks,</i>

32
00:02:46,533 --> 00:02:48,702
<i>I caught a story about 'em</i>
<i>on the news.</i>

33
00:02:48,769 --> 00:02:51,938
Reporter: <i>The world's</i>
<i>first full‐dive VRMMORPG</i>

34
00:02:52,005 --> 00:02:53,306
<i>to use the NerveGear,</i>

35
00:02:53,373 --> 00:02:55,542
<i>the machine</i>
<i>that revolutionized VR gaming,</i>

36
00:02:55,609 --> 00:02:57,477
<i>was called "Sword Art Online."</i>

37
00:02:57,544 --> 00:03:01,648
<i>In 2022, tragedy struck</i>
<i>right when the game launched.</i>

38
00:03:01,715 --> 00:03:03,784
<i>Ten thousand players</i>
<i>had logged on</i>

39
00:03:03,850 --> 00:03:06,987
<i>and suddenly found themselves</i>
<i>trapped in the game.</i>

40
00:03:07,053 --> 00:03:08,622
<i>It took two years to free them,</i>

41
00:03:08,689 --> 00:03:11,257
<i>and in the end,</i>
<i>4,000 players had died.</i>

42
00:03:11,324 --> 00:03:13,927
<i>Consequently,</i>
<i>the public perception of VR</i>

43
00:03:13,994 --> 00:03:15,428
<i>was that it was dangerous,</i>

44
00:03:15,495 --> 00:03:18,298
<i>and no one thought</i>
<i>it would survive the backlash.</i>

45
00:03:18,364 --> 00:03:22,102
<i>The NerveGear rig</i>
<i>was recalled and destroyed.</i>

46
00:03:22,168 --> 00:03:23,970
<i>But when the AmuSphere</i>
<i>hit the market,</i>

47
00:03:24,037 --> 00:03:26,306
<i>along with the license‐free</i>
<i>developer's package</i>

48
00:03:26,372 --> 00:03:29,776
<i>called "the Seed,"</i>
<i>interest in VR picked up again.</i>

49
00:03:29,843 --> 00:03:33,547
<i>Soon, new games made</i>
<i>with the Seed began popping up</i>

50
00:03:33,614 --> 00:03:36,750
<i>with such frequency, it seemed</i>
<i>everyone had forgotten</i>

51
00:03:36,817 --> 00:03:39,553
<i>the horrors</i>
<i>of the SAO Incident entirely.</i>

52
00:03:39,620 --> 00:03:42,589
<i>Once again, players</i>
<i>could leave reality behind</i>

53
00:03:42,656 --> 00:03:46,326
<i>and experience a different life</i>
<i>with all five of their senses,</i>

54
00:03:46,392 --> 00:03:48,328
<i>but, this time,</i>
<i>in complete safety.</i>

55
00:03:48,394 --> 00:03:50,897
‐ That's what I want,
a different life.

56
00:03:50,964 --> 00:03:52,866
‐ [yawns]

57
00:03:52,933 --> 00:03:56,436
Girl: No way!
You're pulling my leg!

58
00:03:56,503 --> 00:03:58,404
Sorry, Kohi,
but you're the last girl

59
00:03:58,471 --> 00:04:00,507
I ever expected
to be into VR games.

60
00:04:00,574 --> 00:04:03,209
So what makes you
so interested in 'em now, huh?

61
00:04:03,276 --> 00:04:05,411
You met a boy in Tokyo,
a cute gamer boy.

62
00:04:05,478 --> 00:04:07,413
‐ N‐No, I didn't meet anyone.

63
00:04:07,480 --> 00:04:09,583
I just thought I'd try
playing one, is all.

64
00:04:09,650 --> 00:04:11,718
And since you play 'em
all the time, Miyu,

65
00:04:11,785 --> 00:04:13,754
I thought
I could pick your brain.

66
00:04:13,820 --> 00:04:16,322
‐ Go on! Pick away!
My brain's open for picking

67
00:04:16,389 --> 00:04:18,559
Don't be shy. Ask me anything.

68
00:04:18,625 --> 00:04:21,394
‐ They're not that dangerous
to play anymore, are they?

69
00:04:21,461 --> 00:04:22,996
‐ Absolutely not!

70
00:04:23,063 --> 00:04:25,699
The AmuSphere rig's designed
to automatically log players out

71
00:04:25,766 --> 00:04:28,434
if it detects anything janky,
so you don't have to worry

72
00:04:28,502 --> 00:04:30,103
about getting trapped
in games anymore.

73
00:04:30,170 --> 00:04:32,205
Just kick back,
dive in, and rock out.

74
00:04:32,272 --> 00:04:35,175
‐ Um, sorry.
I didn't get any of that.

75
00:04:35,241 --> 00:04:36,610
‐ Honestly.

76
00:04:36,677 --> 00:04:38,244
All right,
here's what you're gonna do.

77
00:04:38,311 --> 00:04:41,247
<i>You're gonna go buy the gear,</i>
<i>and then we'll talk.</i>

78
00:04:41,314 --> 00:04:42,649
‐ Karen: Um...
‐ Yes?

79
00:04:42,716 --> 00:04:45,385
‐ I was wondering if you
had the AmuSphere in stock,

80
00:04:45,451 --> 00:04:48,655
that and a VR game
called "ALfheim Online."

81
00:04:50,156 --> 00:04:51,658
Miyu: <i>You got it installed?</i>

82
00:04:51,725 --> 00:04:54,494
‐ Mm‐hmm.
All I have to do is log in.

83
00:04:54,561 --> 00:04:58,064
<i>‐ Then log in, be a fairy,</i>
<i>and go on a quest!</i>

84
00:04:59,833 --> 00:05:02,803
<i>I know you're gonna love "ALO"</i>
<i>as much as I do.</i>

85
00:05:02,869 --> 00:05:06,139
<i>You get to fly around and meet</i>
<i>people in this gorgeous world.</i>

86
00:05:06,206 --> 00:05:09,109
<i>It's gonna blow your mind.</i>

87
00:05:09,175 --> 00:05:11,344
‐ Link start.

88
00:05:14,748 --> 00:05:16,883
Game:
<i>Welcome to ALfheim Online.</i>

89
00:05:16,950 --> 00:05:19,886
<i>Please enter</i>
<i>your avatar's name.</i>

90
00:05:21,988 --> 00:05:25,592
<i>Please select which race</i>
<i>you wish to play as.</i>

91
00:05:26,893 --> 00:05:30,531
<i>You selected Sylph,</i>
<i>the wind fairies.</i>

92
00:05:30,597 --> 00:05:32,566
<i>Creating avatar.</i>

93
00:05:43,109 --> 00:05:44,811
‐ Wha?! This is horrible!

94
00:05:44,878 --> 00:05:47,313
[alarm blaring]

95
00:05:47,380 --> 00:05:49,015
Why'd it give me
a tall avatar?!

96
00:05:49,082 --> 00:05:51,618
Miyu: <i>I'm so sorry!</i>
<i>I totally forgot</i>

97
00:05:51,685 --> 00:05:53,319
<i>you had that complex</i>
<i>about your height.</i>

98
00:05:53,386 --> 00:05:57,390
‐ It's okay, but won't it
let me make my own character?

99
00:05:57,457 --> 00:05:59,025
<i>‐ Well, your avatar's</i>
<i>created at random,</i>

100
00:05:59,092 --> 00:06:01,227
<i>so all you can do</i>
<i>is pick a different race</i>

101
00:06:01,294 --> 00:06:02,495
<i>and hope for the best.</i>

102
00:06:02,563 --> 00:06:05,666
‐ Yeah, I don't think
"ALO" is my thing.

103
00:06:05,732 --> 00:06:08,268
<i>‐ Great.</i>
<i>Now you're all traumatized.</i>

104
00:06:08,334 --> 00:06:11,204
<i>Tell you what? Why don't you</i>
<i>convert your character?</i>

105
00:06:11,271 --> 00:06:12,639
‐ What do you mean, "convert"?

106
00:06:12,706 --> 00:06:13,940
<i>‐ Sorry. Converting means</i>

107
00:06:14,007 --> 00:06:15,542
<i>moving your character</i>
<i>to another game.</i>

108
00:06:15,609 --> 00:06:18,144
<i>Your LLENN I. D.</i>
<i>is yours for good now.</i>

109
00:06:18,211 --> 00:06:20,346
<i>You can't take any items</i>
<i>or money with you,</i>

110
00:06:20,413 --> 00:06:21,815
<i>but you just started,</i>

111
00:06:21,882 --> 00:06:23,183
<i>so it's not like</i>
<i>you're losing anything.</i>

112
00:06:23,249 --> 00:06:26,587
‐ Convenient. Okay.
I'll try a different game.

113
00:06:26,653 --> 00:06:28,221
‐ <i>Oh! By the way,</i>

114
00:06:28,288 --> 00:06:30,023
<i>Elza Kanzaki's next concert's</i>
<i>gonna be in Tokyo.</i>

115
00:06:30,090 --> 00:06:32,392
<i>If I can get tickets,</i>
<i>I'm gonna crash at your place.</i>

116
00:06:32,458 --> 00:06:34,460
<i>Cool? Cool. See you!</i>

117
00:06:34,528 --> 00:06:36,663
[monitor beeping]

118
00:06:36,730 --> 00:06:39,533
Computer: <i>Your character</i>
<i>will now be converted.</i>

119
00:06:42,435 --> 00:06:43,369
[alarm beeping]

120
00:06:43,436 --> 00:06:46,106
‐ I'm still tall, damn it!

121
00:06:46,172 --> 00:06:49,009
‐ [alarm beeping]
‐ Now I'm tall and stocky!

122
00:06:51,077 --> 00:06:52,445
That's not even human!

123
00:06:57,183 --> 00:06:59,119
[panting]

124
00:07:02,856 --> 00:07:03,890
[groans]

125
00:07:03,957 --> 00:07:07,060
<i>‐ Your character</i>
<i>will now be converted.</i>

126
00:07:09,495 --> 00:07:11,932
‐ The 37th time's the charm.

127
00:07:11,998 --> 00:07:15,736
Please work.
Please work. Please!

128
00:07:22,442 --> 00:07:25,712
She's perfect.

129
00:07:25,779 --> 00:07:27,981
I found it! [squeals]

130
00:07:28,048 --> 00:07:30,450
I found it!
I found it! I found it!

131
00:07:30,517 --> 00:07:34,454
I'm so cute,
super cute and little!

132
00:07:34,521 --> 00:07:37,524
[laughing]

133
00:07:37,591 --> 00:07:38,792
‐ Damn, she's teeny.

134
00:07:38,859 --> 00:07:40,761
‐ Yeah. I wonder
if she's even a girl.

135
00:07:40,827 --> 00:07:42,696
Man: What,
they let kids in here now?

136
00:07:42,763 --> 00:07:44,197
Man #2:
She's a little cutie‐pie!

137
00:07:44,264 --> 00:07:46,667
Man #3: I didn't know
you can get a preteen avatar.

138
00:07:46,733 --> 00:07:47,901
Man #4: Nah, that's an NPC.

139
00:07:47,968 --> 00:07:49,803
‐ [thinking] <i>I'm so happy!</i>

140
00:07:49,870 --> 00:07:52,205
<i>Finally, I get to be</i>
<i>short and cute.</i>

141
00:07:52,272 --> 00:07:55,008
<i>Finally, I'm LLENN!</i>

142
00:07:55,075 --> 00:07:56,943
[laughs]

143
00:07:57,010 --> 00:08:00,146
Hang on. What kind
of game is this anyway?

144
00:08:07,087 --> 00:08:08,321
Where am I?

145
00:08:08,388 --> 00:08:09,823
‐ Glad you could
make it, maggot!

146
00:08:09,890 --> 00:08:11,291
‐ Who are you calling a maggot?

147
00:08:11,357 --> 00:08:14,528
‐ You, but I was wrong.
You're just a dung beetle

148
00:08:14,595 --> 00:08:17,497
with the personality
of a maggot! Now listen up!

149
00:08:17,564 --> 00:08:20,601
This world is infested
with horrifying monsters,

150
00:08:20,667 --> 00:08:23,303
rampaging robots, and players
who love murdering.

151
00:08:23,369 --> 00:08:25,872
It's my job to teach you
the skills you need

152
00:08:25,939 --> 00:08:29,242
to survive here, even if I
have to kill you to do it!

153
00:08:29,309 --> 00:08:30,476
‐ I don't‐‐

154
00:08:30,544 --> 00:08:32,312
‐ You will answer
with a "Yes, ma'am"!

155
00:08:32,378 --> 00:08:33,614
‐ Yes, ma'am!

156
00:08:33,680 --> 00:08:36,517
‐ So, dung beetle,
why the hell are you here?

157
00:08:36,583 --> 00:08:39,185
‐ I wanted to be
a cute girl, is all.

158
00:08:39,252 --> 00:08:40,587
‐ You came here to survive!

159
00:08:40,654 --> 00:08:42,989
And here, you need
one of these to survive.

160
00:08:43,056 --> 00:08:46,159
Tell me, do you know
what this is called?

161
00:08:46,226 --> 00:08:47,628
‐ A gun, ma'am?

162
00:08:47,694 --> 00:08:50,864
‐ Correct. You're pretty sharp
for a dung beetle.

163
00:08:50,931 --> 00:08:51,832
‐ [sighs]

164
00:08:51,898 --> 00:08:54,535
‐ You can use
two types of guns here.

165
00:08:54,601 --> 00:08:56,570
One's optical.
The other's live‐ammo.

166
00:08:56,637 --> 00:08:58,705
Your basic optical gun is light.

167
00:08:58,772 --> 00:09:01,307
It shoots longer distances
with accuracy.

168
00:09:01,374 --> 00:09:05,011
The energy packs are a breeze
to swap out, too.

169
00:09:05,078 --> 00:09:08,148
The drawback is, if you
fire it at another player

170
00:09:08,214 --> 00:09:11,051
and their shield's up,
it only does half the damage.

171
00:09:11,117 --> 00:09:12,052
‐ Uh...

172
00:09:12,118 --> 00:09:14,588
‐ And then
there's live‐ammo guns.

173
00:09:17,223 --> 00:09:19,492
The bullets they fire
have actual mass

174
00:09:19,560 --> 00:09:22,663
and can rip through shields
like a hot knife through butter,

175
00:09:22,729 --> 00:09:24,765
but their trajectory's
affected by wind,

176
00:09:24,831 --> 00:09:26,132
and the mags can get heavy.

177
00:09:26,199 --> 00:09:28,635
If you're fighting
monsters in the field,

178
00:09:28,702 --> 00:09:29,836
use an optical gun.

179
00:09:29,903 --> 00:09:31,672
Use live‐ammo guns on players.

180
00:09:31,738 --> 00:09:32,706
You got all that?!

181
00:09:32,773 --> 00:09:33,874
‐ Yes, I think‐‐

182
00:09:33,940 --> 00:09:36,076
‐ "Yes," what?!
‐ Yes, ma'am!

183
00:09:36,142 --> 00:09:37,043
‐ I will now teach you

184
00:09:37,110 --> 00:09:39,279
the basics
of how to handle a gun.

185
00:09:39,345 --> 00:09:40,781
‐ Wh‐What are you doing?!

186
00:09:40,847 --> 00:09:42,516
‐ That is the Bullet Line.

187
00:09:42,583 --> 00:09:44,651
It shows up
when you or your enemy

188
00:09:44,718 --> 00:09:46,186
puts a finger on the trigger.

189
00:09:46,252 --> 00:09:48,622
It shows a bullet's path,
and if you see it,

190
00:09:48,689 --> 00:09:50,223
you either fire
at its origin point

191
00:09:50,290 --> 00:09:53,259
or get the hell out of the way.
You got it?!

192
00:09:53,326 --> 00:09:54,260
‐ Yes, ma'am!

193
00:09:54,327 --> 00:09:55,662
‐ Keep your elbows in,

194
00:09:55,729 --> 00:09:58,431
hold her steady,
and squeeze the trigger.

195
00:09:58,498 --> 00:10:02,168
That is the Bullet Circle.
It shows the area you'll hit.

196
00:10:02,235 --> 00:10:04,204
When you fire,
your bullet will land

197
00:10:04,270 --> 00:10:06,740
at a random point
inside that circle.

198
00:10:06,807 --> 00:10:09,075
Fire your weapon!

199
00:10:09,142 --> 00:10:10,811
[gunshot]

200
00:10:10,877 --> 00:10:13,213
‐ I'm impressed.
Of all the dung beetles

201
00:10:13,279 --> 00:10:15,882
scuttling on the dung heap,
you're at the bottom.

202
00:10:15,949 --> 00:10:17,350
I'll make a prediction.

203
00:10:17,417 --> 00:10:20,621
Once you start playing,
you won't last five seconds!

204
00:10:20,687 --> 00:10:22,422
If you wanna live, shoot!

205
00:10:22,488 --> 00:10:24,991
That's it! Fire! Fire! Fire!

206
00:10:25,058 --> 00:10:27,327
The only way to survive here
is to kill!

207
00:10:28,629 --> 00:10:29,930
Don't forget that!

208
00:10:33,199 --> 00:10:35,902
The size of the circle
fluctuates with every heartbeat.

209
00:10:35,969 --> 00:10:38,839
Take aim, calm down, and fire.

210
00:10:39,873 --> 00:10:41,842
Nice shot, dung beetle.

211
00:10:41,908 --> 00:10:44,945
At least we know you're
totally worthless as a sniper.

212
00:10:50,350 --> 00:10:53,119
That is the most random shooting
I've ever seen.

213
00:10:53,186 --> 00:10:55,188
I guess the submachine gun's
your weapon.

214
00:10:55,255 --> 00:10:58,324
Not bad, for a dung beetle,
dung beetle!

215
00:10:58,391 --> 00:11:01,895
I'll show you how
to use knives in combat next.

216
00:11:01,962 --> 00:11:03,496
‐ Y‐Yes, ma'am!

217
00:11:03,564 --> 00:11:05,566
‐ Watch close.
‐ <i>Oh, my gosh.</i>

218
00:11:05,632 --> 00:11:08,034
<i>Could this game be</i>
<i>any more intense?</i>

219
00:11:11,605 --> 00:11:12,806
Karen: <i>Even so, I decided</i>

220
00:11:12,873 --> 00:11:14,474
<i>to keep on playing</i>
<i>"Gun Gale Online."</i>

221
00:11:14,541 --> 00:11:17,911
<i>Not only did I get to be</i>
<i>short and cute as LLENN,</i>

222
00:11:17,978 --> 00:11:19,112
<i>but I already went through</i>

223
00:11:19,179 --> 00:11:20,614
<i>the hassle</i>
<i>of starting the game.</i>

